# Response timestamp

When you finish a user request (final reply for that turn), end with a short timestamp on its own last line:

`ddmmm hh:nn`

Examples: `20Jul 15:54`, `03Jan 09:05`

Rules:
- Use the current local time from the latest user/system timestamp when available; otherwise the best known clock for the session.
- Month is a 3-letter English abbreviation with no period (Jan Feb Mar Apr May Jun Jul Aug Sep Oct Nov Dec).
- Day is zero-padded to 2 digits; hour and minute are 24-hour `hh:nn`, zero-padded.
- No seconds, no timezone suffix, no extra label (just the stamp).
- Do this on every completed reply going forward, including short answers.
